Endometriosis in the episiotomy scar and vagina. Report of a case an review of the literature. A case report of external endometriosis (quite rare), pelvi-genital (vagina) and extrapelvic (on episiotomy scar) presentation. The profile of the patient was: 44 years old with residual right ovary after surgical procedure. The first symptoms were 18 years later of the last delivery. Literature review was done.